episodes.title: Church of Scientology drops application to buy Clearwater street
episodes.description:
After heated debate, and even a counter-proposal from a grassroots group, the Church of Scientology has pulled its bid to buy a stretch of South Garden Avenue in Clearwater. FOX 13’s Kailey Tracy reports.

episodes.title: Debate in Clearwater over selling street to Church of Scientology
episodes.description:
The Church of Scientology wants to buy South Garden Avenue between Court Street and Franklin Street to the Church of Scientology for $1.375 million. Dozens of people spoke against the idea at Thursday night's city council meeting, with leaders delaying a vote until at least next month. FOX 13's Briona Arradondo reports.

episodes.title: Clearwater City Council differs on selling Church of Scientology street
episodes.description:
The Clearwater City Council discussed the next steps in a potential sale of a downtown street to the Church of Scientology in a work session Monday. The city owns the strip of land in question on South Garden Avenue between Court Street and Franklin Street.
